---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { totalIdeas, clusters } from '../data/clusters.js';
const path = '/about/';
---
<Base
  title="About ideeeas, validated ideas, openly reasoned"
  description="Why ideeeas exists: a growing, honest library of validated startup and side-project ideas with the reasoning shown, not hidden."
  path={path}
>
  <article class="wrap-narrow py-20">
    <div class="text-sm text-fog prompt">cat about.md</div>
    <h1 class="reveal in mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-extrabold text-text">About <span class="amber">ideeeas</span></h1>
    <p class="reveal in mt-6 text-lg text-text/85 leading-relaxed">
      The hard part of building something was never the building, it is choosing what to build. The internet is full of "100 business ideas" lists that are really just nouns with the word "app" attached. None of them tell you whether anyone actually wants the thing, how hard it is to make, or how it earns.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal mt-4 text-text/80 leading-relaxed">
      ideeeas is the opposite of an idea-spam list. Every idea here is structured the same way: a real demand signal, an honest difficulty rating, a specific monetisation path, a realistic time-to-MVP, and the single first step you should take to validate it before writing a line of code.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal mt-4 text-text/80 leading-relaxed">
      The library currently holds {totalIdeas} ideas across {clusters.length} collections, and it grows every week. Ideas are starting points, not promises, the value is in the reasoning, so you can adapt it to your own skills, budget and market.
    </p>
    <h2 class="reveal mt-10 font-display text-xl font-bold text-text"><span class="green">#</span> how it stays honest</h2>
    <ul class="reveal mt-4 space-y-2 text-text/80 list-none pl-0">
      <li><span class="green mr-2">-</span>Demand signals come from observable behaviour, searches, communities, existing spend, not wishful thinking.</li>
      <li><span class="green mr-2">-</span>Difficulty and time estimates assume a competent solo builder, and we say when something is genuinely hard.</li>
      <li><span class="green mr-2">-</span>Some outbound tool links are affiliate links. They never change which tools we recommend.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-8">
      <a href="/ideas/" class="spark-link font-semibold">Browse the full idea library →</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
